# Frontend Standards (`frontend/`)

## Stack

- Next.js 14+ with App Router (project root: `frontend/`)
- Tailwind CSS; shadcn/ui; Lucide React
- **Data**: REST calls to **FastAPI** at `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (Bearer token from Supabase session when endpoints are protected)
- **Design**: [docs/DESIGN.md](mdc:docs/DESIGN.md) (*The Aperture Experience*, Google Stitch) is canonical; align **Figma** handoff to the same tokens. Use skill **`design-aperture`** and Figma MCP when connected

## Component Patterns

- Functional components with TypeScript
- Use `"use client"` only when client interactivity is needed
- Server Components by default for static/SSR; use server-side fetch to internal APIs if you add Next route handlers
- Custom hooks in `frontend/src/hooks/` or `frontend/hooks/`

## File Structure (typical)

```text
frontend/
  src/
    app/           # App Router pages
    components/
      ui/          # shadcn
    hooks/
    lib/           # API client, Supabase browser client, utils
    types/         # TS types — mirror FastAPI/Pydantic contracts
```

## Styling

- Tailwind utility-first; responsive mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- **Dark-first:** the product spec is dark-primary (`docs/DESIGN.md`); map palette to CSS variables / `theme.extend`
- **Typography:** Manrope (display/headlines), Inter (body/labels) per `docs/DESIGN.md`
- **No-line rule:** avoid opaque 1px section borders; use surface tiers and tonal separation
- Prefer Figma tokens only when they match `docs/DESIGN.md`

## Performance

- `next/image` for images
- `dynamic()` for heavy client-only widgets
- `loading.tsx` for Suspense boundaries
